IBADAN – The Chairman Senate Committee on Local Content and lawmaker representing Oyo Central Senatorial District, Senator Teslim Folarin has extended his goodwill message to a former governor of Lagos State and national leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC) on the occasion of his 70th birthday anniversary. Folarin, in a statement he personally signed and made available to journalists on Tuesday stated that he adored the former governor for his unwavering commitment to the unity, peace and progress of Nigeria. “On the auspicious occasion of your 70th birthday anniversary, I heartily rejoice with Your Excellency on behalf of my family and good people of Oyo Central Senatorial District. “I join your family, friends, business associates and well-wishers to thank Almighty God for your life and to pray that He continues to bless you with robust health and imbue you with His continued guidance and protection.” The former Senate Leader described Jagaban of Borgu as a man of excellence and a true democrat who dedicated his life to the service to humanity, an advocate of good governance and the development of democracy in Nigeria.